## Risk Notes

- **No database migration needed.** `ProviderSummaryResponse` is used only at PDF generation time — the structured content is generated fresh at Step 5 and immediately rendered. It is never persisted to the database.
- **`extra="forbid"` on `ProviderSummaryResponse`** means if the LLM returns a `closing` field after this change, validation will hard-fail. This is the correct behavior — it enforces that the prompt and model stay in sync.
- **`build_export_pdf`** in `pdf.py` contains a `"Symptom Pattern Summary"` heading that is intentionally left unchanged — it is a different document and out of scope for this PRD.